01:01.961 --> 01:05.123
[ Tires Screeching ]

01:05.230 --> 01:07.165
D'oh!
[ Screams ]

01:08.868 --> 01:12.827
## [ Humming ]

01:23.683 --> 01:25.583
[ Homer's Voice ]
Hey, Bart-Bart...

01:25.685 --> 01:30.384
looks like a beautiful day to
swipe some ''pic-i-nic'' baskets.

01:30.490 --> 01:33.015
[ Bart's Voice ]
But, ''Homi,'' Ranger Ned's not gonna like that.

01:33.126 --> 01:35.185
I'll handle Ranger Ned.

01:35.295 --> 01:38.787
After all, I'm smarter
than the average bear.

01:38.898 --> 01:41.298
Well, hello there, Ho-didilly-omi.

01:41.401 --> 01:43.995
Well, I'm afraid I'm gonna have
to ask you to hand over that-

01:44.104 --> 01:46.004
[ Shouting ]

01:46.106 --> 01:49.269
Gee, Homi, it's not very nice
to maul Ranger Ned.

01:49.375 --> 01:51.605
- You want some of this?
- Uh-uh.

01:51.711 --> 01:54.339
- [ Shouting ]
- [ Groaning ]

01:54.447 --> 01:56.347
[ Growling ]

01:56.449 --> 01:58.508
- Dad, wake up! Wake up!
- Dad, wake up!

01:58.618 --> 02:01.781
[ Moans ]
I was having the most wonderful dream.

02:01.888 --> 02:04.322
I had a hat and a tie,
with no pants on.

02:04.424 --> 02:07.120
Yeah, yeah. Anyway, you promised
to take us to the lake.

02:07.227 --> 02:10.627
I promise you lots of things.
That's what makes me such a good father.

02:10.729 --> 02:12.925
Actually keeping promises
would make you a good father.

02:13.032 --> 02:15.967
- No, that would make me a great father.
- So Are we going to the lake?

02:16.069 --> 02:18.731
Yes, we'll go to the darn lake.

02:18.838 --> 02:21.432
Now go back to bed. It's 4:00 a.m.

02:22.809 --> 02:26.336
Aw, 4:00 a.m.? Now I'll never get back to-
[ Snoring ]

02:26.446 --> 02:29.244
## [ Singing Cartoon Theme Song ]

02:29.349 --> 02:33.251
Hey, you shouldn't have oughta
taken my banana, Mr. Peebles.

02:33.353 --> 02:35.548
[ Roars, Hoots ]

02:39.425 --> 02:41.393
- [ Horns Honking ]
- <i>[ Marge ] Wow.!</i>

02:41.494 --> 02:44.088
It looks like the lake
is the place to be, huh?

02:44.197 --> 02:47.100
Well, if we'd left at 4:00 a.m
like I wanted to-

02:47.100 --> 02:47.725
Well, if we'd left at 4:00 a.m
like I wanted to-

02:47.834 --> 02:49.859
Dad, you really should be
watching the road.

02:49.969 --> 02:52.267
- Hey, Homer. Enough traffic for you?
- [ Neck Cracks ]

02:52.372 --> 02:54.602
- Homer, your spine.
- [ Cracks ]

02:54.707 --> 02:57.005
Hey, pfft. Screw this.

02:57.110 --> 02:59.943
Hang on, everyone.
We're taking the old Simpson shortcut.

03:00.046 --> 03:02.173
- <i>[ Tires Squeal ]</i>
- [ Homer] So long, suckers.

03:02.282 --> 03:04.944
[ Bart ]
Whoa!

03:05.051 --> 03:08.214
[ Chuckles ]
Eat my dust, suckers.

03:08.321 --> 03:10.619
<i>[ Marge ]</i>
<i>Stop calling everyone suckers.</i>

03:10.723 --> 03:13.317
## [ Homer Scatting ]

03:13.426 --> 03:15.553
Hmm.
[ Chomps ]

03:15.662 --> 03:18.392
Ugh! Pesticides.
[ Chomps ]

03:18.498 --> 03:20.523
Carbamate, if I'm not mistaken.

03:20.633 --> 03:22.533
Yep. Carbamate.

03:22.635 --> 03:24.762
- [ Marge ] Tree!
- I see it.

03:25.872 --> 03:28.864
Hmm. This is such a secluded area.

03:28.975 --> 03:31.569
I wonder who lives in that house.

03:31.678 --> 03:33.908
<i>[ Homer ]</i>
<i>Way out in the sticks like this?</i>

03:34.013 --> 03:35.913
It could only be hillbillies.

03:36.015 --> 03:38.074
So I suppose that's
a hillbillyJacuzzi.

03:38.184 --> 03:40.812
Yep. That's where
they cook up their vittles.

03:40.987 --> 03:43.285
[ Chattering ]

03:44.390 --> 03:46.358
[ Laughs ]

03:47.860 --> 03:50.795
- [ Rod And Todd Giggling ]
- Hey, here come the Simpsons.

03:50.897 --> 03:54.856
Now be careful, Homer. There's a fella
in the sand right in front of you.

03:54.968 --> 03:56.868
[ Shouts ]

03:57.971 --> 04:00.201
Okay, remember where we parked.

04:00.306 --> 04:02.240
<i>[ Ned ]</i>
<i>Homer, is that my muffler?</i>

04:02.342 --> 04:05.709
There you go. And I assume
you've read the boat safety manual.

04:05.812 --> 04:09.179
Oh, yeah. Couldn't put it down.
Come on, boy. Let's get me a six-pack.

04:09.282 --> 04:12.479
Uh, sir, you can't operate a boat
under the influence of alcohol.

04:12.585 --> 04:14.712
Oh, that sounds like a wager to me.

04:14.821 --> 04:17.289
- Life jackets?
- Check.

04:17.390 --> 04:18.357
- Tow rope?
- Secure.

04:18.458 --> 04:20.255
- Skier?
- Ready.

04:20.360 --> 04:22.294
Here we go.

04:22.395 --> 04:24.829
She's down.

04:24.931 --> 04:27.832
- Oh, look at it go.
- Stay there, honey.

04:27.934 --> 04:29.902
<i>We'll come back for you.</i>

04:33.273 --> 04:35.264
[ Screams ]

04:38.745 --> 04:40.542
- How's he doing?
- I don't know.

04:40.647 --> 04:42.774
I think Dad might be
a little heavy for parasailing.

04:42.882 --> 04:46.511
Faster, Marge! Faster.
The snapping turtles are massing.

04:47.687 --> 04:49.587
- Heads up! Coming through.
- [ Clamoring ]

04:49.689 --> 04:51.554
Hey, volleyball.
Can I play later?

04:51.658 --> 04:53.626
Hi, Apu.

04:53.726 --> 04:57.628
Oh, dear. You have ruined my work,
you flying fat man.

04:57.730 --> 04:59.630
- [ Screeching ]
- [ Clamoring ]

04:59.732 --> 05:01.199
Hey!

05:01.301 --> 05:03.360
[ Sighs ]

05:04.971 --> 05:08.839
Step on it, Mom. Dad's signaling
that he wants to go higher.

05:08.941 --> 05:11.341
[ Gurgling ]
Higher.

05:11.444 --> 05:13.639
[ Spits ]
Bye-bye, ''fishies.''

05:13.746 --> 05:16.340
Higher. Higher!

05:16.449 --> 05:18.280
I'm soaring-

05:18.384 --> 05:21.717
Soaring majestically, like
a candy wrapper caught in an updraft.

05:21.821 --> 05:23.880
Higher, Marge. Higher!

05:23.990 --> 05:26.083
- It won't go any.
- Higher, I say.

05:26.192 --> 05:29.218
I wanna soar higher
than any man has ever soared.

05:29.329 --> 05:32.230
I wanna look down
on the clouds with contempt.

05:32.332 --> 05:34.562
I wanna sneer at God's creation...

05:34.667 --> 05:36.635
and spit on his- Uh-oh.

05:39.038 --> 05:41.563
[ Whimpering ]
Lower! Lower!

05:41.674 --> 05:45.542
- There goes my turn.
- [ Whimpering ]

05:45.645 --> 05:47.772
This is not good.

05:47.880 --> 05:51.475
[ Whimpers, Gasps ]
Aw, nuts.

05:51.584 --> 05:53.677
[ Shouting ]

05:57.023 --> 05:58.957
[ Buzzing ]

05:59.058 --> 06:01.754
Huh? What? Oh, already?

06:01.861 --> 06:05.126
- <i>[ Woman Gasps ] What the hell</i>-
- Sorry, lady.

06:05.231 --> 06:07.495
[ Gasps ]
I know you. You're Kim ''Basin-jer.''

06:07.600 --> 06:09.864
- It's Basinger.
- Oh, my God.

06:09.969 --> 06:12.267
I'm such a huge, huge
fan of yours, Miss ''Basin-jer.''

06:12.372 --> 06:14.272
Thanks. Um, listen.

06:14.374 --> 06:18.174
- You think you could slide over a little?
- Well, I am a married man.

06:18.277 --> 06:21.405
- You're crushing my husband.
- [ Man Groans ]

06:21.514 --> 06:23.448
[ Gasps ]
Billy Baldwin!

06:23.549 --> 06:25.779
I'm Alec Baldwin.
Could you get off me?

06:25.885 --> 06:28.513
So what are you two kids
doing in my neck of the woods?

06:28.621 --> 06:30.851
- Well-
- Wait! Tell me over breakfast.

06:30.957 --> 06:33.255
Who's for pancakes?

06:36.829 --> 06:39.423
Are you sure you don't want to go
to the hospital, Mr. Simpson?

06:39.532 --> 06:41.557
You had an awful lot of glass in you.

06:41.667 --> 06:43.567
Oh, I don't want to be a bother.

06:43.669 --> 06:46.797
Anyway, what are you two big Hollywood stars
doing in good old Springfield?

06:46.906 --> 06:48.999
Sometimes we need
to get away from Hollywood.

06:49.108 --> 06:51.008
L.A. is just so phony.

06:51.110 --> 06:53.704
Well, why don't you just
move to, say, Bethesda?

06:53.813 --> 06:56.839
- Not phony enough.
- What we really like here is the privacy.

06:56.949 --> 06:59.440
Most people don't even know
where Springfield is.

06:59.552 --> 07:02.578
Yeah. Tell you the truth,
I'm not even sure.

07:02.688 --> 07:04.656
We're trying to keep a low profile.

07:04.757 --> 07:06.657
We don't even go to the supermarket.

07:06.759 --> 07:09.250
Yeah, we've been living off
congratulatory muffin baskets.

07:09.362 --> 07:12.627
Blech! Zucchini.

07:12.732 --> 07:16.361
- Don't just put that back in the basket.
- I'm gonna eat it later.

07:16.469 --> 07:18.937
You shouldn't have to survive
on dry, crumbly muffins from...

07:19.038 --> 07:21.233
''the Gersh Agency.''

07:21.340 --> 07:23.831
You should let me do your shopping.

07:23.943 --> 07:26.537
I know where I can get you
some great muffins.

07:26.646 --> 07:29.274
- No more muffins.
- Okay, fine.

07:29.382 --> 07:31.316
But I could do all kinds of stuff for you.

07:31.417 --> 07:33.351
I notice that skylight
in your bedroom's broken.

07:33.453 --> 07:36.445
Yeah, I'm not sure we need
an assistant, Mr. Simpson.

07:36.556 --> 07:38.547
Please. Homer. Come on.

07:38.658 --> 07:42.094
If you let me hang around a while,
I can do all kinds of stuff for ya.

07:42.195 --> 07:44.493
Well, we are down
to our last roll of toilet paper.

07:44.597 --> 07:47.157
And I have been brushing
my teeth with hair gel for a week.

07:47.266 --> 07:49.166
I suppose we could give it a try.

07:49.268 --> 07:51.964
- Yeah, you owe me that much.
- Okay, you're on.

07:52.071 --> 07:54.699
But look- Nobody knows we're in
Springfield, and we wanna keep it that way.

07:54.807 --> 07:56.707
Will you promise to keep our secret?

07:56.809 --> 07:58.902
Absolutely, if you promise to keep mine.

07:59.011 --> 08:01.775
- Okay. What is it?
- I can't read.

08:01.881 --> 08:04.406
But you just read that card
from the Gersh Agency.

08:04.517 --> 08:06.485
I recognized the logo.

08:06.586 --> 08:09.419
## [ Whistling ]

08:09.522 --> 08:11.456
Homie, are you okay?

08:11.557 --> 08:14.424
We've been lookin' all over for you, Dad.
Where did you land?

08:14.527 --> 08:17.928
- Nowhere famous.
- Where'd you get that muffin?

08:18.030 --> 08:19.930
Gersh Agency.

08:25.204 --> 08:29.436
Apu, I'm about to purchase some weird
and fruity items, and I don't want any guff.

08:29.542 --> 08:31.533
First of all, I'll need
the following mushrooms:

08:31.644 --> 08:32.611
- Portobello.
- Yes.

08:32.712 --> 08:33.474
- Porcini.
- Right.

08:33.578 --> 08:34.943
- Chanterelle.
- Uh-huh.

08:35.047 --> 08:38.982
- And Shiitake.
- Okay. We have none of those. What is next?

08:39.085 --> 08:43.044
A gallon of wheatgrass juice, a five-pound
wad of tofu, some jellied zinc...

08:43.155 --> 08:46.181
and a couple of pairs
of $600 sunglasses.

08:46.292 --> 08:49.557
Mr. Simpson, these exotic items
are suspiciously different...

08:49.662 --> 08:51.755
from your usual order
of beer and pork.

08:51.864 --> 08:54.389
- What gives?
- Uh, nothing, nothing.

08:54.500 --> 08:56.559
I'm just broadening my horizons.

08:56.669 --> 09:00.196
By the way, do you have extra-wide
bumper stickers for a Humvee?

09:02.275 --> 09:05.711
Wow. You got everything, Homer-
Even the Oscar polish.

09:08.314 --> 09:11.613
- [ Squeaking ]
- Honey, why don't you give that thing a rest?

09:11.717 --> 09:13.617
You're taking the finish off.

09:13.719 --> 09:17.052
When you win one,
you can take care of it however you want.

09:17.156 --> 09:19.420
Whoo-hoo. Meow.

09:19.525 --> 09:22.119
- <i>[ Doorbell Rings ]</i>
- I'll get it. I'll get it.

09:23.629 --> 09:26.063
- Yes?
- Hi. I'm Ron Howard.

09:26.165 --> 09:28.759
- Ron Howard?
- Yeah. I'm looking...

09:28.868 --> 09:30.836
for Alec Baldwin and Kim Basinger.

09:30.937 --> 09:33.405
Alec Baldwin and Kim Basinger?

09:33.506 --> 09:36.373
Oh, hey, Ron. We heard you were
looking for a place in Springfield.

09:36.475 --> 09:39.740
Yeah, well, it's the only town in America
that'll let me fish with dynamite.

09:39.845 --> 09:41.938
Uh-What's with him?

09:42.048 --> 09:44.573
Oh, that's just Homer.
He's a new friend of ours.

09:44.684 --> 09:47.881
Really? You giant stars
consider me a friend?

09:47.987 --> 09:52.549
Well, for the first time
in my life I feel like I'm somebody.

09:52.658 --> 09:55.422
Ronny, are you also my close friend?

09:55.528 --> 09:58.759
[ Sniffs ]
Do I smell vodka? And wheatgrass?

09:58.864 --> 10:00.764
It's called a lawn mower. I invented it.

10:00.866 --> 10:02.766
- You want one?
- Yeah, okay.

10:02.868 --> 10:05.701
- And I'll have a rum and zinc.
- Ooh, I'll have one of those too.

10:05.805 --> 10:10.401
- Hey, can I crash here tonight?
- Sure. We'll all stay.

10:12.478 --> 10:15.606
A cell phone?

10:15.715 --> 10:17.649
Last Thursday's <i>Variety?</i>

10:17.750 --> 10:19.843
- <i>[ Door Closes ]</i>
- <i>##[ Whistling ]</i>

10:19.952 --> 10:22.477
[ Gasps ]
I'll do that. You go upstairs and have a beer.

10:22.588 --> 10:25.216
Homer, when did you
become a member of PETA?

10:25.324 --> 10:28.122
Well, you know me.
I love animals-

10:28.227 --> 10:30.127
Beef, chicken, veal.

10:30.229 --> 10:33.596
If you're not part of the solution, Marge,
you're part of the problem.

10:33.699 --> 10:36.133
- That's not what PETA stand-
- [ Ringing ]

10:36.235 --> 10:38.601
- Imagine Films.
- Hmm?

10:38.704 --> 10:41.639
A, uh, division of, um, Homer Co.

10:41.741 --> 10:43.936
- <i>##[ Disco Beat ]</i>
- <i>And lift. And strain.</i>

10:44.043 --> 10:45.943
And hyperextend.

10:46.045 --> 10:49.344
Keep those knees rigid.
Jerk that lower back.

10:49.448 --> 10:52.542
Homer, I'm- I'm feeling some
sharp pains in my neck.

10:52.652 --> 10:54.620
That' right, force it.
Whip that neck.

10:54.720 --> 10:57.382
Um, does anybody know
where this came from?

10:57.490 --> 11:01.893
Oh, <i>there's</i> that movie script I wrote.

11:01.994 --> 11:04.895
- Where did you find it?
- On my pillow.

11:04.997 --> 11:07.795
The important thing is,
it's got the perfect part for you.

11:07.900 --> 11:09.800
Either one of you.

11:09.902 --> 11:11.870
It's about a killer-robot
driving instructor...

11:11.971 --> 11:14.735
who travels back in time
for some reason.

11:14.840 --> 11:16.774
Ron Howard's attached to direct.

11:16.876 --> 11:18.810
- I am not.
- Well, he expressed an interest.

11:18.911 --> 11:20.811
- No, I didn't.
- Did too.

11:20.913 --> 11:23.006
- I did not.
- You lie!

11:23.115 --> 11:25.913
Yeah, Homer, um,
most movie scripts are 1 20 pages.

11:26.018 --> 11:27.986
This is only 1 7...

11:28.087 --> 11:30.988
and several of the pages are
just drawings of the time machine.

11:31.090 --> 11:34.821
- So you're saying you don't want
to star in my movie?
- I'm sorry, Homer.

11:34.927 --> 11:38.795
Well, if Alec is out, I'm out too.
You're on your own, Potsie.

11:38.898 --> 11:41.765
<i>''The Terminizer:An Erotic Thriller. ''</i>

11:41.867 --> 11:43.801
<i>[ Chattering, Laughter ]</i>

11:43.903 --> 11:46.997
So I'm in the grocery store the other day,
buying some cotton balls.

11:47.106 --> 11:50.075
- The absorbent kind?
- You got that right, my friend.

11:50.176 --> 11:53.737
- [ Laughing ]
- I round the corner and I head
down the ointment aisle...

11:53.846 --> 11:55.746
when who should I spot-

11:55.848 --> 11:57.907
None other than Kent Brockman.

11:58.017 --> 12:00.815
The local news guy?
''Mr. Channel 6''?

12:00.920 --> 12:03.684
- <i>[ Chattering ]</i>
- My God! What I'd give to meet him.

12:03.789 --> 12:05.950
- Oh, they don't come much bigger than that.
- <i>[ Blows Raspberries ]</i>

12:06.058 --> 12:08.652
Kent Brockman? Please.

12:08.761 --> 12:11.286
Oh, what? I suppose you've seen a bigger star.

12:11.397 --> 12:14.889
- I might have.
- Come on, make with a name.

12:15.000 --> 12:18.367
[ Groans ]
I can't. I promised I wouldn't.

12:25.377 --> 12:27.572
You've got to keep
our secret, Homer.

12:27.680 --> 12:29.671
Homer, we're out of vodka.

12:29.782 --> 12:32.307
Tell the people, Homer.
They have a right to know...

12:32.418 --> 12:34.352
about the celebrity summer house.

12:34.453 --> 12:36.421
- Who the hell are you?
- What do you care?

12:36.522 --> 12:38.956
I'm telling you what you want to hear.

12:39.058 --> 12:41.618
All right, I'm gonna
let you guys in on something.

12:41.727 --> 12:45.788
But you've got to keep it
much more secret than I did.

12:45.898 --> 12:47.525
[ Grunts ]

12:47.633 --> 12:50.124
- [ Grunts ]
- [ Grunts ]

12:50.236 --> 12:54.070
Yes! In your freckled face, Howard.

12:55.174 --> 12:57.199
- Unbelievable.
- What?

12:57.309 --> 12:59.209
Nothing, nothing. Good hustle.

13:01.947 --> 13:05.644
- <i>[ Rhythmic Rumbling ]</i>
- My God-The lemonade. Look at the lemonade.

13:05.751 --> 13:10.085
- <i>[ Rumbling Continues ]</i>
- Uh-oh.

13:10.189 --> 13:12.282
[ Chattering ]

13:12.391 --> 13:15.792
Hey, look at that.
Isn't that something?

13:15.895 --> 13:18.455
Quick- Everybody inside.

13:20.566 --> 13:22.966
The shuttlecock-
Where's the shuttlecock?

13:23.068 --> 13:26.970
- [ Chattering ]
- [ Panting ]

13:27.072 --> 13:29.666
<i>[ Chattering Continues ]</i>

13:31.710 --> 13:34.338
Arr. I loved <i>Splash,</i> Mr. Howard.

13:34.446 --> 13:39.145
- It was totally, uh, uh, arr. [ Chuckles ]
- Uh, Miss Basinger?

13:39.251 --> 13:42.015
Those red pumps you wore
in <i>L.A. Confidential</i> were fabulous.

13:42.121 --> 13:45.522
Where can I get a pair for my, uh, mother?
She wears a 1 2 double-E.

13:45.624 --> 13:48.787
Alec, Alec- Regarding that so-called
silent propulsion system...

13:48.894 --> 13:50.794
in <i>The Hunt for Red October</i>-

13:50.896 --> 13:53.160
I printed out a list
of technical errors...

13:53.265 --> 13:55.199
which I think you'd
enjoy discussing.

13:56.302 --> 13:59.499
Somebody must have
told them we live here.

13:59.605 --> 14:01.470
I'm looking at you, Horshack.

14:01.574 --> 14:03.804
Homer, how could you?

14:03.909 --> 14:06.400
Okay, okay, it was me.
I'm sorry I blew your secret.

14:06.512 --> 14:08.707
But you don't know
what it's like to be a nobody.

14:08.814 --> 14:11.874
I just wanted to bask
in your reflected glory.

14:11.984 --> 14:14.452
Reflected glory!

14:14.553 --> 14:17.283
Homer, you betrayed our confidence.

14:17.389 --> 14:20.290
I just don't think
we can be friends anymore.

14:20.392 --> 14:24.385
- But where will I bask?
- Anywhere but here.

14:24.496 --> 14:27.226
Come on, Ron. We're not wanted here.

14:29.001 --> 14:30.935
All right, I'll go.

14:31.036 --> 14:33.971
But the next time you want someone
to remind you which brother is which...

14:34.073 --> 14:36.769
- or smell your hair while you're sleeping-
- [ Gasps ]

14:36.876 --> 14:40.744
just remember, old Homer
won't be here anymore.

14:40.846 --> 14:42.746
- <i>[ Clamoring ]</i>
- <i>[ Moe ] Hey, come on.!</i>

14:42.848 --> 14:44.873
[ Sideshow Mel ]
Wait a minute. Somebody's coming out.

14:44.984 --> 14:48.511
- Who is it? Is it anybody?
- No, no. It's nobody.

14:48.621 --> 14:50.680
Throw your stones. It's nobody.

14:50.789 --> 14:52.950
[ Clamoring ]

14:59.298 --> 15:03.359
Oh, how could Alec and Kim
just cut me out of their lives?

15:03.469 --> 15:05.960
Homer, you haven't
touched your food.

15:07.806 --> 15:11.401
When Kim makes a Manwich,
she uses focaccia bread.

15:11.510 --> 15:13.842
And would it kill you
to put some fennel in it?

15:13.946 --> 15:18.508
Alec Baldwin? Wow! That is
the coolest person you've ever been fired by.

15:18.617 --> 15:21.552
- What was it like at their house?
- Oh, it was so great.

15:21.654 --> 15:23.645
I didn't have to fake it with them.

15:23.756 --> 15:26.224
I was actually excited
to hear about their day.

15:26.325 --> 15:29.419
- I washed the dog today.
- Was it the dog from the <i>Beethoven</i> movies?

15:29.528 --> 15:32.986
- Of course not.
- [ Groans ] Our dog isn't famous.

15:33.098 --> 15:35.931
And you kids aren't exactly
John and Joan Cusack.

15:36.035 --> 15:38.902
And you-You couldn't open a movie
if your life depended on it.

15:39.004 --> 15:41.404
I'm about ready
to ankle this family.

15:41.507 --> 15:45.238
Ankle? Focaccia?
What are you talking about?

15:45.344 --> 15:48.905
See? It's like we don't even speak
the same language anymore.

15:49.014 --> 15:52.711
The only one who understands me
is that guy who married Martha Raye.

15:52.818 --> 15:55.685
Don't blame us, Dad. The celebrities
are the ones who canned you.

15:55.788 --> 15:58.757
Hmm. She may not be famous,
but she's right.

15:58.857 --> 16:01.690
Those big-shot stars
used me up and spit me out.

16:01.794 --> 16:04.285
I did their laundry.
Got their pictures developed.

16:04.396 --> 16:06.296
Took their garbage to the dump.

16:06.398 --> 16:09.526
And I <i>still</i> got
a carful of their crap.

16:09.635 --> 16:12.035
Crap, eh?

16:13.138 --> 16:15.538
<i>[ Chattering ]</i>

16:16.675 --> 16:19.269
Hey, is it too late
to see the movie stars?

16:19.378 --> 16:21.573
No, no.Just, uh, hop that fence...

16:21.680 --> 16:23.807
sneak up and, uh,
peek in the window there.

16:23.916 --> 16:25.816
All right.

16:25.918 --> 16:27.818
- [ Crackling ]
- [ Groans ]

16:27.920 --> 16:30.286
[ Chuckles ]
I never get tired of that.

16:30.389 --> 16:32.289
<i>[ Horn Honks ]</i>

16:32.391 --> 16:34.621
<i>[ Homer On Loudspeaker ]</i>
<i>Attention, starstruck fools.</i>

16:34.727 --> 16:37.821
Step right up and see
the world's greatest mobile collection...

16:37.930 --> 16:40.831
of Alec and Ron and ''Kim-o-rabilia.''

16:40.933 --> 16:44.164
- [ Chattering ]
- Only five- No wait. Ten dollars.

16:44.269 --> 16:47.898
- You heard right. Twenty dollars.
- <i>[ Lenny ] Homer, me first. Come on, man.</i>

16:48.007 --> 16:49.907
[ Chattering ]

16:50.009 --> 16:52.603
[ Barney ]
Oh! Hundred-year-old stuff.

16:52.711 --> 16:55.407
Hey, it's Alec Baldwin's
Medic Alert bracelet.

16:55.514 --> 16:58.950
That's right, ''Mr. Tough Guy''
can't handle a little penicillin.

16:59.051 --> 17:00.951
Oh, and look at this.

17:01.053 --> 17:06.286
We can't even pay our bills,
and they're drinking Royal Crown Cola.

17:06.392 --> 17:10.192
- Hey, hey. Go easy on the celebrities, huh?
- Yeah. What gives you the right?

17:10.295 --> 17:12.194
- Leave 'em alone.
- We love celebrities.

17:12.297 --> 17:14.857
Oh, yeah? What have they
ever done for you?

17:14.967 --> 17:18.925
When was the last time Barbra Streisand
cleaned out your garage?

17:19.038 --> 17:22.940
And when it's time to do the dishes,
where's Ray Bolger?

17:23.041 --> 17:24.942
I'll tell ya.

17:25.044 --> 17:28.343
Ray Bolger is lookin' out for Ray Bolger!

17:30.749 --> 17:33.877
<i>Oh, look. Wasn't that a fun weekend?</i>

17:33.986 --> 17:36.921
Yeah. Homer was a pretty good guy.

17:37.022 --> 17:39.616
And we just tossed him out
like a Golden Globe award.

17:39.725 --> 17:42.523
I've got to admit, I miss the way
he used to tuck us in...

17:42.628 --> 17:44.528
and kiss us on the forehead.

17:44.630 --> 17:47.565
- Forehead?
- Oh, maybe I should have made his movie.

17:47.666 --> 17:49.657
Yeah. It wasn't that bad.

17:49.768 --> 17:51.668
I mean, the script
might even work...

17:51.770 --> 17:53.704
if you got rid of the talking pie.

17:53.806 --> 17:55.797
What, are you crazy?
It's a buddy picture.

17:55.908 --> 17:58.502
Without the pie, it would just be me
on screen for two hours.

17:58.610 --> 18:00.510
Oh, yeah, and you'd hate that.

18:00.612 --> 18:03.911
No, no, no. You can't lose the pie.
The pie is your heart.

18:04.016 --> 18:06.314
Okay, okay. Keep the damn pie.

18:06.418 --> 18:08.909
The point is, we weren't fair to Homer.

18:09.021 --> 18:11.922
He screwed up, but he deserves
another chance.

18:12.024 --> 18:13.992
Yeah. Everyone makes mistakes.

18:14.093 --> 18:17.620
I mean, we'd want another chance
if one of us ever made a bad film, right?

18:17.729 --> 18:20.323
<i>[ Birds Singing ]</i>

18:21.934 --> 18:23.868
<i>[ Ducks Quacking ]</i>

18:28.674 --> 18:31.575
I'm really looking forward
to seeing Homer again.

18:31.677 --> 18:34.145
He always has the most
interesting odors.

18:35.714 --> 18:37.614
[ High-Pitched Voice ]
Ooh, look at me.

18:37.716 --> 18:40.583
I'm Kim Basinger,
the big movie star.

18:40.686 --> 18:44.247
I'm so beautiful.
I think I'm so great.

18:44.356 --> 18:47.120
I'm too important to take
Homer to the Oscars.

18:47.226 --> 18:48.693
- What the-
- [ Screams ]

18:48.794 --> 18:51.490
Got to go. Thank you for supporting
the Museum of Hollywood Jerks.

18:52.664 --> 18:56.395
- Let's get him.
- And this time it's personal.

18:56.502 --> 18:58.732
What? It <i>is</i> personal.

18:58.837 --> 19:00.964
He's got our underpants.

19:02.074 --> 19:05.066
[ Tires Screeching ]

19:05.177 --> 19:09.409
- [ Horn Honking ]
- I'll never outrun them in a museum.

19:09.515 --> 19:12.040
- Pull over, you maniac.
- No!

19:12.151 --> 19:15.143
Just jump over there, Alec.
It's not that far.

19:15.254 --> 19:17.313
Yeah, you're a big
screen tough guy.

19:17.422 --> 19:20.357
Uh, gee, I'd love to, but I'm not really
wearing the right shoes.

19:20.459 --> 19:22.689
[ Imitates Chicken ]

19:22.794 --> 19:24.694
Fine.

19:27.099 --> 19:30.091
- [ Grunts ]
- [ Screams ]

19:30.202 --> 19:33.569
[ Laughing ]
Hey, I made it. All by myself.

19:33.672 --> 19:36.140
Hey, were you watching,
sweetheart? I made it!

19:36.241 --> 19:39.301
Ow! Aaah! My watch is caught.

19:39.411 --> 19:42.209
Oh, for the love of- Hold on.

19:42.314 --> 19:46.273
- Can you drive?
- Not well, but I'll give it a shot.

19:49.154 --> 19:51.122
- [ Grunts ]
- <i>[ Thump ]</i>

19:51.223 --> 19:53.020
- Oh, God!
- <i>[ Tire Screeching ]</i>

19:53.125 --> 19:54.990
[ Kim Screaming ]

19:55.093 --> 19:57.118
[ Both Screaming ]

19:58.530 --> 20:01.727
I guess it's up to me.

20:03.468 --> 20:06.460
- [ Groaning ]
- [ Both ] Ron!

20:07.573 --> 20:11.100
- You killed Ron Howard.
- Okay, I'll stop.

20:11.210 --> 20:13.735
<i>[ Gavel Banging ]</i>

20:17.182 --> 20:21.448
- Mr. Simpson, do you have
anything to say for yourself?
- Yes, I do.

20:21.553 --> 20:24.420
I believe that famous people
have a debt to everyone.

20:24.523 --> 20:27.583
If celebrities didn't want
people pawing through their garbage...

20:27.693 --> 20:31.993
and saying they're gay, they shouldn't have
tried to express themselves creatively.

20:34.399 --> 20:36.799
In closing, you people must realize...

20:36.902 --> 20:40.599
that the public owns you for life,
and when you're dead...

20:40.706 --> 20:44.608
you'll all be in commercials,
dancing with vacuum cleaners.

20:44.710 --> 20:46.974
Thank you, Your Honor.

20:47.079 --> 20:50.480
Mr. Simpson, you are forbidden
to come within 500 miles...

20:50.582 --> 20:53.380
of any celebrity, living or dead.

20:53.485 --> 20:55.749
[ All ]
Whoo-hoo!

20:56.788 --> 20:58.813
Well, I'll always have
my crank calls.

20:58.924 --> 21:00.824
[ Beeping ]

21:00.926 --> 21:03.121
Hello? Old lady from <i>Titanic?</i>

21:03.228 --> 21:06.220
You stink!
[ Giggles ]

21:08.367 --> 21:12.736
And it grows to a powerful,
emotional climax...

21:12.838 --> 21:15.102
when the father has to choose...

21:15.207 --> 21:18.506
which one of his children will live...

21:18.610 --> 21:22.011
and which one will die.

21:22.114 --> 21:24.309
- Pass.
- [ Groans ]

21:24.416 --> 21:26.748
- What else you got?
- Uh-

21:26.852 --> 21:29.082
Well, there is this one thing.

21:29.187 --> 21:31.781
It's about a killer-robot
driving instructor...

21:31.890 --> 21:34.290
that travels back in time
for some reason.

21:34.393 --> 21:36.361
- I'm listening.
- Okay, okay.

21:36.461 --> 21:38.725
Well, you see, this robot-

21:38.830 --> 21:40.798
He's got a heartbreaking
decision to make...

21:40.899 --> 21:44.733
about whether his
best friend lives or dies.

21:45.804 --> 21:48.796
- Eh.
- His best friend's a talking pie.

21:48.907 --> 21:51.603
Sold! Howard, you've done it again.

21:51.710 --> 21:52.244
<i>##[ Man Singing ]</i>

21:52.244 --> 21:54.371
<i>##[ Man Singing ]</i>

22:37.756 --> 22:40.088
- [ Murmuring ]
- Shh!

22:40.192 --> 22:42.592
<i>[ Ron Howard ]</i>
<i>Homer, we're out of vodka.</i>

